description.value: Blue glazed composition 'reis' shabti of Pinudjem I: this is a typical overseer shabti; the individual is dressed in a lappet wig with a uraeus and a robe of the type worn by the living. He has a modelled face with traced eyes and a beard. His right arm is flexed across his chest and holds a stylized whip, ready to bring down on the backs of any reluctant workers. The short text on his apron identifies him as the 'sehedj', the Osiris-king Pinedjem, beloved of Amun.
